Paper: hep-th/0107130

Date: 2001-07-16

Title: Gravity in Dynamically Generated Dimensions

Authors: Myron Bander

Comments: 7 pages, LaTeX (Revtex)

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D64 (2001) 105021

A theory of gravity in $d+1$ dimensions is dynamically generated from atheory in $d$ dimensions. As an application we show how $N$ dynamically coupledgravity theories can reduce the effective Planck mass.